MatchedRegion.Text: Fine-tuning does not always results in improvement of student models e.g., M1 student drop from 75.39 to 74.37 when using M5 as teacher.

MatchedRegions.transcript: We asked several questions related to the performance of the model where it is fine-tuned in the block-by-block setting compared to that when trained normally.
From the result in this figure, we can see that in all cases, the student model is able to outperform the teacher.
